parameters: What should we do with him?
\n<...>Do you like to suffer, to see your friends die?
\n<...>Then just stay here and DO NOT climb up the tree.
\n<Thomas>If climbing up the tree will help me find my friends,
\n<...>Trust me, you forgot about that day for a reason.
\n<Thomas>...So you just want me to stay here and do nothing?
\n<...>What do you what me to do, sir?
\n<...>I'm here to serve you and my master.
\n<...>We're not allowed to touch it, sir.
\n<Thomas>And you've never asked yourself what is up there?
\n<...>Why would I? Master clearly said that it won't do
\n<Thomas>Who cares about what she says? You're free
\n<...>Freedom only leads to suffering and regrets...
\n<...>Like now you're thinking about returning your
memories... And no matter what decision you'll make
\n<...>Because you can't know the future nor possible outcomes
But...she... I can trust her my life.
\n<...>Are you sure you're want to go up there, sir?
Believe me, you won't like what you'll see.
\n<Thomas>Those are my friends...I have to know!
No matter what's in there... I have to know...
\n<...>I won't let you. That's for your own good...
